http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Narrow-escape-for-patients-as-fire-erupts-in-hospital/article13988267.ece

Patients at a corporate hospital near Gajuwaka had a narrow escape as fire erupted on the third floor of the building on Thursday afternoon.Sources said that there were about 15 in-patients at the time of the fire and all of them were evacuated immediately.Welding work going on in the building was said to have caused the fire.Following information, fire tenders were called.But by the time they arrived, the situation was brought under control by the hospital staff.Inquiry beginsFire service officials began an inquiry to ascertain the exact cause of the fire and whether fire-fighting equipment was installed by the management, s per the norms.